Class CustomPath

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.shape.Shape
javafx.scene.shape.Path
com.simulus.view.intersection.CustomPath
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class CustomPath extends javafx.scene.shape.Path
An extension to the JavaFX Path class. Allows storing additional information like the tiles a path starts/ends on, its length in pixel, the direction the path ends in and whether the path is active, i.e. whether vehicles are actually allowed to follow the path.

  • Constructor Details

    • CustomPath

      public CustomPath(TurningDirection turn, double pathDistance, Tile st, Tile et, Direction ed, javafx.scene.shape.PathElement... elements)
      Parameters:
      turn - The direction this path turns in
      pathDistance - The length of the path in px
      st - The tile IN FRONT OF the the intersection and the start of the path
      et - The tile BEHIND the intersection and the end of the path
      ed - The direction the car moves into after following the path
      elements - Path(PathElement...)
